text: Rosby is an unincorporated community in Beltrami and Hubbard counties, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== A post office was established at Rosby in 1900, and remained in operation until 1909. The community was named for Ole Rosby, an early Norwegian settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Beltrami County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Hubbard County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: Rosby, Minnesota
